<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="1691" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,661,756]" box="[160,251,661,687]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1691">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,251,661,687]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1691">Remark</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,661,756]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1691">In the female genitalia of this species, ductus bursae have tiny spines in the posterior margin. The number of spines differs between specimens.</paragraph>
