<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="1691" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,800,895]" box="[160,285,800,826]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1691">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1691">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[160,1155,800,895]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1691">
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[688,758,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1691">minuti</emphasis>
(= small), plus the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1062,1120,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1691">spina</emphasis>
(= spine), referring to tiny spines in the posterior margin of female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
